00:12:36,470 --> 00:12:38,510
Gosh, our Hye Yoon is back alive.

268
00:12:39,240 --> 00:12:41,379
(Jung Ah!)

269
00:12:41,380 --> 00:12:43,480
(We'll come back safely!)

270
00:12:44,010 --> 00:12:46,680
(See you later.)

271
00:12:48,150 --> 00:12:51,290
(It's time to look for the turtles.)

272
00:12:52,250 --> 00:12:55,720
(Looking around)

273
00:12:57,590 --> 00:13:01,300
(The turtles aren't seen right away.)

274
00:13:02,260 --> 00:13:07,740
(The ones who wish to see them must find them.)

275
00:13:08,140 --> 00:13:10,870
(She seems to feel uncomfortable with her snorkel.)

276
00:13:11,670 --> 00:13:17,109
(The youngest stops for a while.)

277
00:13:17,110 --> 00:13:19,709
(The older brother steps up.)

278
00:13:19,710 --> 00:13:20,849
(He helps her grab the tube.)

279
00:13:20,850 --> 00:13:22,519
Take it off.

280
00:13:22,520 --> 00:13:23,790
Take it off and shake it.

281
00:13:23,820 --> 00:13:24,949
Bite onto it again.

282
00:13:24,950 --> 00:13:26,019
(The snorkel is put on again.)

283
00:13:26,020 --> 00:13:27,020
Okay.

284
00:13:28,960 --> 00:13:34,230
(He acts as an older brother again with his specialty.)

285
00:13:34,760 --> 00:13:38,100
(The youngest starts exploring again.)

286
00:13:42,600 --> 00:13:45,570
(A turtle is found!)

287
00:13:45,610 --> 00:13:46,980
It's a turtle!

288
00:13:47,510 --> 00:13:48,580
Over there!

289
00:13:50,350 --> 00:13:51,950
(Screaming)

290
00:13:52,180 --> 00:13:53,180
(Amazed)

291
00:13:53,181 --> 00:13:55,080
(The three siblings go wild.)

292
00:13:55,750 --> 00:13:57,289
Hey! Turtle!

293
00:13:57,290 --> 00:13:58,949
(The turtle swims peacefully.)

294
00:13:58,950 --> 00:14:00,190
It's a turtle!

295
00:14:02,690 --> 00:14:05,260
(Awesome!)

296
00:14:05,490 --> 00:14:06,960
It's fascinating!

297
00:14:08,060 --> 00:14:10,530
(Here's something even more fascinating.)

298
00:14:10,870 --> 00:14:11,870
Turtle!

299
00:14:11,871 --> 00:14:13,940
(Two turtles!)

300
00:14:15,500 --> 00:14:16,610
(Kissing)

301
00:14:19,510 --> 00:14:22,239
(It starts eating off the ground...)

302
00:14:22,240 --> 00:14:25,210
(as if nothing happened.)

303
00:14:34,290 --> 00:14:37,430
(The turtles are seen up close for the first time.)

304
00:14:38,390 --> 00:14:43,570
(The three siblings look at them in awe.)

305
00:14:49,870 --> 00:14:53,210
(With the turtle that eats off the ground in peace, )

306
00:14:56,980 --> 00:15:00,120
(they dance.)

307
00:15:01,320 --> 00:15:06,020
(A dance session underwater)

308
00:15:12,090 --> 00:15:15,760
(Dances with Turtles)

309
00:15:19,070 --> 00:15:20,070
(Shouting)

310
00:15:20,071 --> 00:15:21,840
(Exclaiming)

311
00:15:22,540 --> 00:15:23,540
I'm so scared.

312
00:15:23,541 --> 00:15:25,139
- Hurry.
- Here you go.

313
00:15:25,140 --> 00:15:26,140
I got it.

314
00:15:26,640 --> 00:15:28,610
(Dex's camera)

315
00:15:29,010 --> 00:15:30,010
Gosh.

316
00:15:30,950 --> 00:15:33,850
(The turtle is coming up.)

317
00:15:40,520 --> 00:15:43,390
(They meet a turtle that comes up to breathe.)

318
00:15:47,830 --> 00:15:51,170
(We have to see this!)

319
00:15:57,870 --> 00:16:00,210
(Puff)

320
00:16:05,210 --> 00:16:08,020
(Gurgling)

321
00:16:09,550 --> 00:16:12,790
(It's close enough to touch if you stretch out your hand.)

322
00:16:13,790 --> 00:16:17,190
(The turtle's breathing that Dex filmed)

323
00:16:17,290 --> 00:16:18,859
(It's illegal to touch turtles.)

324
00:16:18,860 --> 00:16:20,780
(This was filmed in accordance with local laws.)

325
00:16:21,560 --> 00:16:24,530
(Hello)

326
00:16:32,810 --> 00:16:36,079
(Goodbye)

327
00:16:36,080 --> 00:16:37,279
Unbelievable.

328
00:16:37,280 --> 00:16:39,450
- Oh, my.
- It was so adorable.

329
00:16:40,850 --> 00:16:43,350
- It was very...
- It was so cute.

330
00:16:43,750 --> 00:16:46,089
The turtle must have come up to the surface to breathe.

331
00:16:46,090 --> 00:16:47,359
(I can't believe that I saw a turtle breathe.)

332
00:16:47,360 --> 00:16:48,560
It was amazing.

333
00:16:50,020 --> 00:16:52,089
(While the turtle that had given them a rare sight...)

334
00:16:52,090 --> 00:16:54,160
(went back to grazing, )

335
00:16:54,700 --> 00:16:55,759
(the three siblings arrived on the island safely.)

336
00:16:55,760 --> 00:16:57,430
Okay, thank you.

337
00:16:58,630 --> 00:16:59,799
(Exhausted after swimming)

338
00:16:59,800 --> 00:17:00,800
Okay?

339
00:17:01,170 --> 00:17:03,040
- I'm okay.
- Breathe.

340
00:17:04,440 --> 00:17:06,809
Jun Myun, why are you also speaking to me in English?

341
00:17:06,810 --> 00:17:09,109
I'm speaking to you in English.

342
00:17:09,110 --> 00:17:10,750
(Laughing at Jun Myun's speaking English)

343
00:17:11,010 --> 00:17:12,979
(Collapsing)

344
00:17:12,980 --> 00:17:14,620
- That's right.
- It's so comfortable.

345
00:17:15,750 --> 00:17:16,850
Stay like that.

346
00:17:19,750 --> 00:17:21,820
I'll cover Ms. Actress with a blanket.

347
00:17:21,920 --> 00:17:23,189
Thank you.

348
00:17:23,190 --> 00:17:26,160
(Jun Myun makes her laugh, and Dex covers her with a blanket.)

349
00:17:27,560 --> 00:17:30,170
It was a fun activity at the sea.

350
00:17:30,270 --> 00:17:31,470
- I agree.
- Yes.

351
00:17:31,570 --> 00:17:33,499
- It's rare to see turtles.
- Right.

352
00:17:33,500 --> 00:17:35,260
(They also danced with turtles that summer.)

353
00:17:35,570 --> 00:17:37,310
Gosh, it's so beautiful.

354
00:17:38,170 --> 00:17:41,339
(She's taking a walk on Balicasag Beach.)

355
00:17:41,340 --> 00:17:42,710
Shall we go over there?

356
00:17:45,750 --> 00:17:49,050
(Walking along the white sandy beach)

357
00:17:49,750 --> 00:17:52,690
(With gentle waves drifting in)

358
00:17:54,560 --> 00:17:58,660
(Surrounded by relaxed travelers)

359
00:18:00,160 --> 00:18:04,070
(Both the body and the mind are unwinding.)

360
00:18:04,770 --> 00:18:08,400
(Restoring her energy with a promenade)

361
00:18:09,200 --> 00:18:11,310
(Pausing)

362
00:18:12,470 --> 00:18:14,310
Won't it take a while to get here by swimming?

363
00:18:16,610 --> 00:18:20,180
(Enjoying a picturesque scenery while waiting for the siblings)

364
00:18:20,850 --> 00:18:24,190
(Balicasag, a treasure island for divers)

365
00:18:25,090 --> 00:18:28,920
(At a quaint seaside restaurant)

366
00:18:29,620 --> 00:18:35,430
(People gather, still damp from the water.)

367
00:18:36,360 --> 00:18:40,340
(She's supposed to meet her siblings here.)

368
00:18:41,340 --> 00:18:45,270
(Jung Ah is all alone.)

369
00:18:45,640 --> 00:18:48,740
(The restaurant begins to get crowded with customers.)

370
00:18:49,240 --> 00:18:51,750
(She even sees her dance mates from the same boat.)

371
00:18:52,150 --> 00:18:54,219
(Watching in silence)

372
00:18:54,220 --> 00:18:56,120
I guess they're having a lot of fun.

373
00:18:56,650 --> 00:18:58,350
There's no sight of them.

374
00:19:00,050 --> 00:19:02,189
I'm the only one with separation anxiety.

375
00:19:02,190 --> 00:19:04,430
(While the eldest sister is enduring separation anxiety)

376
00:19:04,560 --> 00:19:06,960
We got to see a turtle that came up.

377
00:19:07,060 --> 00:19:08,459
It was so cute.

378
00:19:08,460 --> 00:19:10,700
- We saw it very close.
- I know.

379
00:19:11,430 --> 00:19:12,800
I also made a wish.

380
00:19:13,170 --> 00:19:14,900
What? What did you wish for?

381
00:19:15,270 --> 00:19:17,439
- A bunch of things.
- I see.

382
00:19:17,440 --> 00:19:18,640
Take a guess.

383
00:19:19,210 --> 00:19:21,640
- Our show's spin-off...
- That it becomes a hit.

384
00:19:22,010 --> 00:19:23,140
For a safe shoot...

385
00:19:23,480 --> 00:19:25,009
I didn't wish for that.

386
00:19:25,010 --> 00:19:26,949
- What?
- What?

387
00:19:26,950 --> 00:19:29,749
A safe shoot for Fresh Off the Sea's spin-off.

388
00:19:29,750 --> 00:19:31,420
You should've wished for that.

389
00:19:31,920 --> 00:19:35,060
That's needless to say. It will go well.

390
00:19:35,860 --> 00:19:37,090
It will be fine.

391
00:19:37,230 --> 00:19:39,560
Did you wish for a girlfriend?

392
00:19:40,060 --> 00:19:41,060
- Jun Myun.
- Yes?

393
00:19:41,061 --> 00:19:42,359
If I tell you, it won't come true.

394
00:19:42,360 --> 00:19:43,899
- That's true.
- Really?

395
00:19:43,900 --> 00:19:45,860
(Wishes only come true when they're kept secret.)

396
00:19:46,270 --> 00:19:48,270
Gosh, look at the sky.

397
00:19:48,700 --> 00:19:50,099
It looks so beautiful.

398
00:19:50,100 --> 00:19:52,109
- Goodness, this is really...
- The sky looks incredible.

399
00:19:52,110 --> 00:19:53,139
(Clear and blue sky that looks just like the transparent sea)

400
00:19:53,140 --> 00:19:54,280
My goodness.

401
00:19:55,110 --> 00:19:57,410
- This is a real getaway.
- Seriously.

402
00:19:58,210 --> 00:20:00,110
We're really on vacation.

403
00:20:02,050 --> 00:20:04,389
- It really feels like a vacation.
- Yes.

404
00:20:04,390 --> 00:20:05,390
(In full vacation mode)

405
00:20:05,391 --> 00:20:07,990
(While they laugh and chat, )

406
00:20:08,760 --> 00:20:09,919
(she's waiting anxiously.)

407
00:20:09,920 --> 00:20:12,290
(When are they coming?)

408
00:20:13,290 --> 00:20:14,299
They're coming.

409
00:20:14,300 --> 00:20:15,300
(She spots Dex.)

410
00:20:15,500 --> 00:20:17,870
(Springing to her feet as she's happy to see him)

411
00:20:17,970 --> 00:20:18,970
Jung Ah.

412
00:20:20,570 --> 00:20:22,469
- How was it?
- It was fun.

413
00:20:22,470 --> 00:20:23,639
I took the boat.

414
00:20:23,640 --> 00:20:24,839
We saw so many turtles.

415
00:20:24,840 --> 00:20:25,840
- Really?
- Yes.

416
00:20:25,841 --> 00:20:28,480
- Was it fascinating?
- There were so many underwater.

417
00:20:29,210 --> 00:20:30,910
Are we done with swimming?

418
00:20:31,380 --> 00:20:32,449
- No.
- We're doing it once more.

419
00:20:32,450 --> 00:20:34,979
We're going in to see some fish. I'm thinking of going in.

420
00:20:34,980 --> 00:20:36,620
You should.

421
00:20:36,720 --> 00:20:39,519
- We came all the way here.
- Will I be able to breathe?

422
00:20:39,520 --> 00:20:41,060
- Of course, Jung Ah.
- Definitely.

423
00:20:41,260 --> 00:20:43,929
The water is really beautiful.

424
00:20:43,930 --> 00:20:45,030
I see.

425
00:20:45,490 --> 00:20:48,160
(Here comes today's meal.)

426
00:20:48,630 --> 00:20:49,799
(Her jaw drops.)

427
00:20:49,800 --> 00:20:50,870
What's this?

428
00:20:51,200 --> 00:20:52,570
(Her eyes are fixed on it.)

429
00:20:53,030 --> 00:20:56,470
(A lavish, unfamiliar feast is laid out before them.)

430
00:20:57,840 --> 00:21:01,080
(On a large banana leaf)

431
00:21:01,240 --> 00:21:02,840
(Fish and meat)

432
00:21:02,940 --> 00:21:03,979
(Fried food)

433
00:21:03,980 --> 00:21:05,049
(Grilled skewers)

434
00:21:05,050 --> 00:21:06,279
(Fruit and more)

435
00:21:06,280 --> 00:21:09,880
(A variety of traditional Filipino dishes with rice)

436
00:21:10,920 --> 00:21:14,860
Oh, my. This is amazing. It looks really beautiful.

437
00:21:15,660 --> 00:21:16,889
Shouldn't we take a photo of it?

438
00:21:16,890 --> 00:21:18,189
Yes, we really should.

439
00:21:18,190 --> 00:21:19,559
We can't eat this anywhere else.

440
00:21:19,560 --> 00:21:21,229
(A sight that you want to save)

441
00:21:21,230 --> 00:21:23,660
- "Bohol." - "Bohol."

442
00:21:24,630 --> 00:21:25,729
Bon appetit.

443
00:21:25,730 --> 00:21:27,100
- Bon appetit.
- Bon appetit.

444
00:21:27,970 --> 00:21:31,009
(Glancing)

445
00:21:31,010 --> 00:21:32,570
Go ahead first, Jung Ah.

446
00:21:33,610 --> 00:21:35,780
(The youngest who's a polite, Confucian girl)

447
00:21:36,780 --> 00:21:39,180
(Then I'll start with fried squid.)

448
00:21:39,780 --> 00:21:43,450
(Deep-fried until crispy that looks mouthwatering)

449
00:21:44,020 --> 00:21:45,449
(How does it taste?)

450
00:21:45,450 --> 00:21:47,690
(Crunchy and chewy)

451
00:21:48,520 --> 00:21:51,890
(The youngest follows the leader and pops one into her mouth.)

452
00:21:51,990 --> 00:21:53,860
(Eyes lighting up)

453
00:21:54,400 --> 00:21:57,200
(Jun Myun follows the trend and takes a bite too.)

454
00:21:57,370 --> 00:21:59,330
Oh, is it fried squid?

455
00:21:59,430 --> 00:22:00,939
- Isn't it good?
- It's good.

456
00:22:00,940 --> 00:22:01,940
This is good.

457
00:22:02,940 --> 00:22:06,170
(Dex also takes a bite.)

458
00:22:06,410 --> 00:22:08,640
(What is Jung Ah's next dish pick?)

459
00:22:10,040 --> 00:22:13,410
(One fish that looks golden and crunchy)

460
00:22:14,550 --> 00:22:18,320
(The Philippines' national fish, grilled milkfish)

461
00:22:18,750 --> 00:22:20,619
(Separating the meat carefully...)

462
00:22:20,620 --> 00:22:22,690
(and putting it into the mouth)

463
00:22:23,420 --> 00:22:25,789
(Nodding)

464
00:22:25,790 --> 00:22:27,700
- It's good.
- It's like grilled fish in Korea.

465
00:22:28,660 --> 00:22:30,029
The fish is also delicious.

466
00:22:30,030 --> 00:22:32,599
The fish is good like grilled fish in Korea.

467
00:22:32,600 --> 00:22:33,600
It's similar.

468
00:22:33,601 --> 00:22:34,970
- Right.
- This is nice.

469
00:22:35,200 --> 00:22:38,670
(They can't stop eating it.)

470
00:22:39,910 --> 00:22:42,339
(After good food, rinse the mouth with sweet pineapple juice.)

471
00:22:42,340 --> 00:22:44,350
Gosh, it's made with real pineapple.

472
00:22:45,410 --> 00:22:46,709
It's real pineapple.

473
00:22:46,710 --> 00:22:49,079
- The pineapple juice is excellent.
- It's made with only pineapple.

474
00:22:49,080 --> 00:22:50,149
It's delicious.

475
00:22:50,150 --> 00:22:51,419
(The food suits everyone's taste.)

476
00:22:51,420 --> 00:22:53,350
This restaurant must be quite good.

477
00:22:53,720 --> 00:22:55,959
Jun Myun, didn't you eat a lot of mangoes before?

478
00:22:55,960 --> 00:22:57,360
- Now...
- Mango isn't...

479
00:22:57,730 --> 00:22:58,970
- a meal.
- That doesn't count.

480
00:22:59,390 --> 00:23:00,529
(What's wrong with this young man?)

481
00:23:00,530 --> 00:23:01,930
Come on. You know better.

482
00:23:02,300 --> 00:23:03,559
Goodness.

483
00:23:03,560 --> 00:23:04,699
(I made a mistake.)

484
00:23:04,700 --> 00:23:06,399
I already have a plan.

485
00:23:06,400 --> 00:23:07,400
- What's your plan?
- What is it?

486
00:23:07,401 --> 00:23:08,739
I'll finish the meal with some mango.

487
00:23:08,740 --> 00:23:09,740
(Her favorite mango comes last.)

488
00:23:09,741 --> 00:23:10,939
She's eating mangoes...

489
00:23:10,940 --> 00:23:13,086
- to her heart's content.
- I'll clean the palate with it.

490
00:23:13,110 --> 00:23:14,870
She's eating mangoes to her heart's content.

491
00:23:14,980 --> 00:23:16,439
I can eat mangoes endlessly.

492
00:23:16,440 --> 00:23:17,449
For me...

493
00:23:17,450 --> 00:23:18,726
(Foodie Jun Myun is a total J when it comes to eating.)

494
00:23:18,750 --> 00:23:20,310
(Here's your mango.)

495
00:23:22,150 --> 00:23:23,380
Have mine too, Jun Myun.

496
00:23:23,820 --> 00:23:25,119
- That's funny.
- Leave a piece for Hye Yoon.

497
00:23:25,120 --> 00:23:26,289
Hand me Dex's mango too.

498
00:23:26,290 --> 00:23:27,889
Are you serious about eating it all?

499
00:23:27,890 --> 00:23:29,960
Of course. Why do you even ask?

500
00:23:30,360 --> 00:23:31,760
Will you be okay?

501
00:23:32,560 --> 00:23:33,660
Gosh, Jung Ah.

502
00:23:33,760 --> 00:23:35,099
I'm starting to get worried.

503
00:23:35,100 --> 00:23:37,129
What if something goes wrong with her?

504
00:23:37,130 --> 00:23:39,470
- Why?
- Here's why.

505
00:23:39,870 --> 00:23:42,500
She had mangoes in the fridge as soon as she got up.

506
00:23:43,740 --> 00:23:46,709
I saw her picking at the mango seed this morning.

507
00:23:46,710 --> 00:23:47,809
You can't do this.

508
00:23:47,810 --> 00:23:49,639
- You'll be in big trouble.
- This is for Hye Yoon.

509
00:23:49,640 --> 00:23:50,779
I don't want any.

510
00:23:50,780 --> 00:23:52,250
You'll go into shock.

511
00:23:53,180 --> 00:23:55,250
What? No way.

512
00:23:55,350 --> 00:23:57,219
I won't go into shock from eating mangoes.

513
00:23:57,220 --> 00:23:58,726
She will go into shock from eating mangoes.

514
00:23:58,750 --> 00:24:00,149
What's wrong with you?

515
00:24:00,150 --> 00:24:03,560
(Jun Myun's love for mangoes is willing to risk a shock.)

516
00:24:03,820 --> 00:24:05,990
Let's go to a mango farm on Wednesday.

517
00:24:06,730 --> 00:24:07,799
For labor.

518
00:24:07,800 --> 00:24:09,199
(We have a mango-friendly worker.)

519
00:24:09,200 --> 00:24:11,130
We'd earn a lot of money that day.

520
00:24:11,570 --> 00:24:13,450
What's the point? She will eat them all anyway.

521
00:24:14,600 --> 00:24:16,470
(The story has a set ending.)

522
00:24:17,410 --> 00:24:18,440
Jung Ah.

523
00:24:18,740 --> 00:24:20,370
I also like mangoes a lot.

524
00:24:21,210 --> 00:24:24,250
Compared to Jun Myun, I'm not someone who likes them.

525
00:24:24,350 --> 00:24:26,349
- I can't say...
- Don't go around and tell people...

526
00:24:26,350 --> 00:24:27,519
- that I like mangoes.
- that you like mangoes.

527
00:24:27,520 --> 00:24:28,749
I can only say...

528
00:24:28,750 --> 00:24:30,349
- that I eat mangoes.
- You know how to eat them.

529
00:24:30,350 --> 00:24:31,350
- I know how to eat them.
- Right.

530
00:24:31,351 --> 00:24:32,719
- This is what it means...
- What's with you?

531
00:24:32,720 --> 00:24:34,919
- to be a mango fan.
- Exactly.

532
