849
00:40:17,560 --> 00:40:19,570
What's your dress code tonight?

850
00:40:20,130 --> 00:40:21,470
(Sighing)

851
00:40:21,740 --> 00:40:24,269
I have an acquaintance who I owed a big time.

852
00:40:24,270 --> 00:40:25,910
And she has a wedding in the Philippines.

853
00:40:26,670 --> 00:40:28,540
(The kettle is on.)

854
00:40:28,810 --> 00:40:31,140
So I've prepared the outfit for the wedding.

855
00:40:31,680 --> 00:40:33,250
Isn't it for a funeral?

856
00:40:33,580 --> 00:40:34,849
(Flustered)

857
00:40:34,850 --> 00:40:36,719
That's an option too.

858
00:40:36,720 --> 00:40:39,720
It's good for both occasions. It's multi-black...

859
00:40:40,550 --> 00:40:42,320
(Turning quickly all of a sudden)

860
00:40:42,590 --> 00:40:43,590
(Laughing)

861
00:40:43,591 --> 00:40:46,559
I'm wearing black. Thank you. I'm Participant One.

862
00:40:46,560 --> 00:40:48,760
Are you giving points? No?

863
00:40:50,200 --> 00:40:51,870
(Sullen)

864
00:40:52,500 --> 00:40:53,930
(The actress leaves the carpet.)

865
00:40:54,900 --> 00:40:57,370
(Another actress heads to the food carpet.)

866
00:41:03,310 --> 00:41:05,950
(With a totally relaxed smile, )

867
00:41:07,280 --> 00:41:09,250
(she walks briskly.)

868
00:41:11,550 --> 00:41:14,350
(This actress is...)

869
00:41:19,360 --> 00:41:23,200
(a former Miss Korea runner-up.)

870
00:41:24,060 --> 00:41:25,799
(Looking)

871
00:41:25,800 --> 00:41:27,270
I have to look at each one.

872
00:41:27,630 --> 00:41:28,770
She's a former Miss Korea.

873
00:41:29,600 --> 00:41:30,716
- We'll take photos.
- Okay.

874
00:41:30,740 --> 00:41:31,740
Please give us a heart.

875
00:41:32,370 --> 00:41:33,370
(An old-style heart)

876
00:41:33,371 --> 00:41:34,809
Please give us a cheek heart.

877
00:41:34,810 --> 00:41:35,980
(Flustered)

878
00:41:36,480 --> 00:41:37,979
(She masters a newer heart too.)

879
00:41:37,980 --> 00:41:40,750
I have a mark on my cheek from the swimming goggles.

880
00:41:40,910 --> 00:41:42,019
(The aftermath of the boat tour)

881
00:41:42,020 --> 00:41:43,979
What's your dress code tonight?

882
00:41:43,980 --> 00:41:46,049
Actually, I wore this,

883
00:41:46,050 --> 00:41:48,689
expecting to go to a high-end restaurant.

884
00:41:48,690 --> 00:41:52,030
So I chose a dress that goes well with wine.

885
00:41:53,030 --> 00:41:55,030
- You look pretty.
- Thank you.

886
00:41:55,200 --> 00:41:57,530
(Will she go to a fancy restaurant as she wishes?)

887
00:41:57,930 --> 00:41:59,030
What's happening?

888
00:41:59,600 --> 00:42:00,700
I'm so nervous.

889
00:42:02,400 --> 00:42:04,900
(An actress enters nervously.)

890
00:42:05,370 --> 00:42:07,140
(Clumsily)

891
00:42:07,210 --> 00:42:08,910
(Shifting her vibe suddenly)

892
00:42:08,980 --> 00:42:10,240
(Laughing)

893
00:42:10,340 --> 00:42:11,440
(Giggling)

894
00:42:11,750 --> 00:42:12,750
(Laughing)

895
00:42:12,751 --> 00:42:13,810
What?

896
00:42:15,180 --> 00:42:16,449
(The first actress to enter the runway...)

897
00:42:16,450 --> 00:42:17,719
(while snickering)

898
00:42:17,720 --> 00:42:19,490
(Focused)

899
00:42:20,120 --> 00:42:23,090
From left to center. Forward. Downward.

900
00:42:23,420 --> 00:42:24,460
To the right.

901
00:42:25,190 --> 00:42:26,489
Thank you.

902
00:42:26,490 --> 00:42:28,860
- We'll have a brief photo session.
- Okay.

903
00:42:30,560 --> 00:42:31,670
Please give us a heart.

904
00:42:32,200 --> 00:42:33,400
(Laughing)

905
00:42:33,570 --> 00:42:35,340
What's your dress code today?

906
00:42:35,440 --> 00:42:37,569
Today, I wanted...

907
00:42:37,570 --> 00:42:40,340
to look like a little princess.

908
00:42:40,710 --> 00:42:43,080
Her nickname is My Melody Princess.

909
00:42:43,480 --> 00:42:44,739
(Boasting about her little sister)

910
00:42:44,740 --> 00:42:46,509
Yes. I've prepared to look...

911
00:42:46,510 --> 00:42:48,279
like My Melody Princess or a little princess.

912
00:42:48,280 --> 00:42:49,379
Aren't your shoulders too exposed?

913
00:42:49,380 --> 00:42:51,149
My shoulders? They are...

914
00:42:51,150 --> 00:42:52,719
The sleeves are crawling up a bit.

915
00:42:52,720 --> 00:42:53,880
It's making me uncomfortable.

916
00:42:54,050 --> 00:42:55,059
(Actresses' competition)

917
00:42:55,060 --> 00:42:56,989
Well... Right. I don't think I can cook.

918
00:42:56,990 --> 00:42:58,530
So I have to eat out today.

919
00:42:59,160 --> 00:43:00,760
(Declaring a boycott on cooking tonight)

920
00:43:02,200 --> 00:43:04,429
(I'm going to eat out tonight.)

921
00:43:04,430 --> 00:43:05,630
Thank you.

922
00:43:07,100 --> 00:43:08,100
Come here.

923
00:43:09,300 --> 00:43:10,300
What are we doing?

924
00:43:11,300 --> 00:43:12,770
Will Jin Young be over the top?

925
00:43:12,940 --> 00:43:15,279
- I can't wait.
- I didn't get to see him.

926
00:43:15,280 --> 00:43:16,800
He was in the restroom the whole time.

927
00:43:17,410 --> 00:43:18,649
(He's busy in the makeup room getting ready for the finale.)

928
00:43:18,650 --> 00:43:20,910
(Rustling)

929
00:43:21,480 --> 00:43:23,749
- Why were you nervous?
- I don't know. I was so nervous.

930
00:43:23,750 --> 00:43:24,750
(Chatting while waiting for the finale)

931
00:43:24,751 --> 00:43:25,890
(Opening abruptly)

932
00:43:28,720 --> 00:43:30,319
(Glancing)

933
00:43:30,320 --> 00:43:31,660
- I knew it.
- I knew it.

934
00:43:33,273 --> 00:43:34,712
(Glancing)

935
00:43:34,713 --> 00:43:36,083
- I knew it.
- I knew it.

936
00:43:40,653 --> 00:43:42,953
(Did you expect it?)

937
00:43:43,053 --> 00:43:44,053
(Screaming)

938
00:43:44,223 --> 00:43:45,653
(Here's the cheer.)

939
00:43:46,853 --> 00:43:49,263
(Walking confidently in a black suit)

940
00:43:50,793 --> 00:43:53,293
(Looking somewhat uncomfortable in contrast)

941
00:43:53,433 --> 00:43:56,703
(Uncomfortable)

942
00:43:57,763 --> 00:43:58,772
That look on his face.

943
00:43:58,773 --> 00:43:59,832
(Awkward)

944
00:43:59,833 --> 00:44:01,193
What's with the look on your face?

945
00:44:01,733 --> 00:44:03,842
(He has a food-carpet fright.)

946
00:44:03,843 --> 00:44:05,102
Please look to the left side too.

947
00:44:05,103 --> 00:44:06,112
(Photo session)

948
00:44:06,113 --> 00:44:08,043
I think he's feeling very awkward too.

949
00:44:10,013 --> 00:44:11,013
What?

950
00:44:11,613 --> 00:44:13,453
(That's correct.)

951
00:44:13,553 --> 00:44:15,012
(Feeling extremely awkward, he gives two thumbs up.)

952
00:44:15,013 --> 00:44:16,022
I think he's broken.

953
00:44:16,023 --> 00:44:18,223
Thank you all for coming today.

954
00:44:19,293 --> 00:44:23,193
I've come with a heavy heart, expecting a big award.

955
00:44:23,523 --> 00:44:24,643
That's how I've gotten here.

956
00:44:24,993 --> 00:44:27,369
Right. And the concept of my outfit is an agent from "Man in Black."

957
00:44:27,393 --> 00:44:29,403
I'll complete a mission.

958
00:44:31,733 --> 00:44:33,373
- Thank you.
- What is this?

959
00:44:33,573 --> 00:44:35,543
- Cool.
- You've prepared a lot.

960
00:44:35,843 --> 00:44:37,143
He came prepared.

961
00:44:37,243 --> 00:44:39,112
- He was well-prepared.
- He wrote a script.

962
00:44:39,113 --> 00:44:40,312
No, that's not true.

963
00:44:40,313 --> 00:44:41,673
Now, we'll go straight...

964
00:44:42,043 --> 00:44:43,242
- Let's play the game.
- to the game.

965
00:44:43,243 --> 00:44:44,482
Okay. Quickly.

966
00:44:44,483 --> 00:44:46,253
Right away? Is it all over already?

967
00:44:46,453 --> 00:44:48,382
- We'll get ready for the game.
- Okay.

968
00:44:48,383 --> 00:44:50,553
(Please forget about how I looked just now.)

969
00:44:52,293 --> 00:44:54,092
(Back to reality)

970
00:44:54,093 --> 00:44:55,093
It's game time.

971
00:44:55,094 --> 00:44:57,163
Gosh. I'm nervous.

972
00:44:57,563 --> 00:44:59,192
- This is Fresh off the Sea, right?
- What?

973
00:44:59,193 --> 00:45:00,932
- Is this Fresh off the Sea?
- Yes, it is.

974
00:45:00,933 --> 00:45:04,302
Yes. I've come here with a very heavy heart.

975
00:45:04,303 --> 00:45:05,432
I was so nervous.

976
00:45:05,433 --> 00:45:09,273
Hye Yoon and I fixed our makeup more than we did...

977
00:45:09,373 --> 00:45:11,043
at an actual award show.

978
00:45:11,573 --> 00:45:13,843
- We were fierce.
- We kept fixing our makeup.

979
00:45:14,713 --> 00:45:16,942
Seriously. I can't cook now.

980
00:45:16,943 --> 00:45:18,042
- Seriously.
- Not now.

981
00:45:18,043 --> 00:45:19,282
I don't want to cook.

982
00:45:19,283 --> 00:45:21,153
How can we cook in this outfit?

983
00:45:21,583 --> 00:45:23,452
I can't see the ingredients because of my sunglasses.

984
00:45:23,453 --> 00:45:26,223
I can't even grab a plate from the top shelf right now.

985
00:45:27,153 --> 00:45:28,992
- Exactly.
- Yes.

986
00:45:28,993 --> 00:45:30,623
Please. We have to go out.

987
00:45:30,823 --> 00:45:32,462
When you look at the back,

988
00:45:32,463 --> 00:45:35,133
the schedule for the dinner on the second day is empty.

989
00:45:35,663 --> 00:45:38,032
- Yes.
- What? That's right.

990
00:45:38,033 --> 00:45:41,202
Will you fill the empty slot with a low-end meal coupon?

991
00:45:41,203 --> 00:45:42,402
(Low-end meal coupon)

992
00:45:42,403 --> 00:45:44,372
Or will you fill it with a high-end meal coupon?

993
00:45:44,373 --> 00:45:45,573
(High-end meal coupon)

994
00:45:46,073 --> 00:45:47,613
Or is it going to be cooking?

995
00:45:48,783 --> 00:45:50,713
Today's game will decide it.

996
00:45:51,243 --> 00:45:52,283
Yes.

997
00:45:52,513 --> 00:45:55,453
Right. The game with the meal coupon at stake is...

998
00:45:56,253 --> 00:45:58,893
Close-Up Food Quiz.

999
00:45:59,493 --> 00:46:01,253
Are you going to show only part of a dish?

1000
00:46:01,393 --> 00:46:04,122
Actually, while you were on Fresh off the Sea,

1001
00:46:04,123 --> 00:46:06,963
you cooked various dishes.

1002
00:46:07,063 --> 00:46:08,632
- And you enjoyed eating them too.
- Yes.

1003
00:46:08,633 --> 00:46:12,803
We'll use the dishes you had on this show.

1004
00:46:13,433 --> 00:46:15,743
(We've cooked so much.)

1005
00:46:21,213 --> 00:46:23,443
(Countless dishes by the siblings)

1006
00:46:23,613 --> 00:46:25,512
We'll give you a total of ten questions.

1007
00:46:25,513 --> 00:46:26,813
- Okay.
- Of the ten questions,

1008
00:46:27,213 --> 00:46:30,082
when you get 0 to 3 questions,

1009
00:46:30,083 --> 00:46:32,122
you have to cook at home.

1010
00:46:32,123 --> 00:46:33,522
(Scoffing)

1011
00:46:33,523 --> 00:46:36,392
From 4 to 7 correct answers,

1012
00:46:36,393 --> 00:46:37,822
we'll give you a low-end meal coupon.

1013
00:46:37,823 --> 00:46:40,293
- From eight, it's the high-end one.
- Yes.

1014
00:46:41,033 --> 00:46:42,202
We have to get almost all of them right.

1015
00:46:42,203 --> 00:46:44,532
That's right. We can only miss two.

1016
00:46:44,533 --> 00:46:46,732
- Are you ready?
- Yes, we're ready.

1017
00:46:46,733 --> 00:46:49,903
Then we'll give you the first question.

1018
00:46:59,953 --> 00:47:01,712
- Rice grains.
- That's corn.

1019
00:47:01,713 --> 00:47:02,993
- Corn in rice.
- Isn't that it?

1020
00:47:03,053 --> 00:47:06,122
- I put corn kernels in...
- Okay.

1021
00:47:06,123 --> 00:47:07,823
Samgyetang. No, it wasn't samgyetang.

1022
00:47:08,393 --> 00:47:10,793
I made a chicken dish with corn.

1023
00:47:11,063 --> 00:47:12,333
- Was it chicken soup?
- Yes.

1024
00:47:12,593 --> 00:47:14,232
I made something like that with corn, didn't I?

1025
00:47:14,233 --> 00:47:15,563
I think so.

1026
00:47:15,833 --> 00:47:16,902
Isn't that a corn kernel?

1027
00:47:16,903 --> 00:47:18,973
- But for me, on the other hand, - Yes.

1028
00:47:19,073 --> 00:47:21,803
It looks like webfoot octopus roe.

1029
00:47:22,773 --> 00:47:24,643
Right. The protruding roe.

1030
00:47:24,743 --> 00:47:26,503
What's the yellow thing in the middle, then?

1031
00:47:27,643 --> 00:47:29,382
I'm confident that it's corn.

1032
00:47:29,383 --> 00:47:31,083
- It's corn.
- It is corn.

1033
00:47:31,413 --> 00:47:33,353
The ones around it are rice grains.

1034
00:47:33,453 --> 00:47:34,512
(Analysis complete.)

1035
00:47:34,513 --> 00:47:36,052
- It's samgyetang with corn.
- Yes.

1036
00:47:36,053 --> 00:47:37,282
- I think so.
- Samgyetang made with corn.

1037
00:47:37,283 --> 00:47:39,622
- We harvested corn that day.
- Yes.

1038
00:47:39,623 --> 00:47:40,652
It was the hottest day on Earth.

1039
00:47:40,653 --> 00:47:42,563
- Yes.
- It was in Goseong.

1040
00:47:42,963 --> 00:47:45,093
- We got it.
- We got it. It's samgyetang.

1041
00:47:46,393 --> 00:47:47,862
Samgyetang with corn.

1042
00:47:47,863 --> 00:47:48,933
The answer is...

1043
00:47:49,803 --> 00:47:51,763
(Kimchi and bean sprout porridge)

1044
00:47:51,863 --> 00:47:52,872
(Kimchi and bean sprout porridge)

1045
00:47:52,873 --> 00:47:55,233
- It's bean sprout porridge.
- Are those bean sprouts?

1046
00:47:55,573 --> 00:47:57,343
Was it the head of a bean sprout?

1047
00:47:57,703 --> 00:47:58,772
It wasn't corn.

1048
00:47:58,773 --> 00:48:00,013
Is it bean sprout ramyeon?

1049
00:48:00,313 --> 00:48:02,042
- We made bean sprout porridge.
- I think it's porridge.

1050
00:48:02,043 --> 00:48:03,482
We used the leftovers for breakfast.

1051
00:48:03,483 --> 00:48:05,213
- We made it.
- It was Namhae.

1052
00:48:05,313 --> 00:48:06,833
It was when Hwang Jung Min visited us.

1053
00:48:07,353 --> 00:48:09,683
(For the first guest of the show, Hwang Jung Min, )

1054
00:48:10,283 --> 00:48:13,393
(this dish showed the siblings' overeating restaurant.)

1055
00:48:14,053 --> 00:48:15,823
(Man-in-Black mode is off.)

1056
00:48:16,093 --> 00:48:17,573
It's kimchi and bean sprout porridge.

1057
00:48:18,123 --> 00:48:19,662
Right. I found it extremely hot.

1058
00:48:19,663 --> 00:48:22,232
- Why did you zoom it in like that?
- Seriously.

1059
00:48:22,233 --> 00:48:23,339
(Because that's what this quiz is.)

