(Unmindful of his surroundings, he just eats the skewers.)

1567
01:07:17,810 --> 01:07:18,839
- Look. You need...
- What is that?

1568
01:07:18,840 --> 01:07:19,909
To clench your fist like this.

1569
01:07:19,910 --> 01:07:21,749
Why would that go up? That never happened to me.

1570
01:07:21,750 --> 01:07:23,519
- You make a fist like that?
- It sticks out, right?

1571
01:07:23,520 --> 01:07:25,920
(He keeps the routine of eating rice after eating a skewer.)

1572
01:07:26,120 --> 01:07:27,519
You must like this, Dex.

1573
01:07:27,520 --> 01:07:28,989
He likes this.

1574
01:07:28,990 --> 01:07:30,089
The sausage-like skewer.

1575
01:07:30,090 --> 01:07:32,120
(Dex is in love with chorizo.)

1576
01:07:32,290 --> 01:07:33,859
It's like Korean tteokgalbi.

1577
01:07:33,860 --> 01:07:35,259
- Yes.
- You're right.

1578
01:07:35,260 --> 01:07:37,199
- It tastes like tteokgalbi.
- Yes, it's like tteokgalbi.

1579
01:07:37,200 --> 01:07:39,700
(He finishes the last skewer.)

1580
01:07:39,760 --> 01:07:40,770
I'm done eating.

1581
01:07:42,570 --> 01:07:44,369
- I'm full.
- That was a good meal.

1582
01:07:44,370 --> 01:07:45,400
I'm so full.

1583
01:07:46,200 --> 01:07:47,870
- Are you done eating?
- Yes.

1584
01:07:48,340 --> 01:07:50,509
I'll make an announcement regarding tomorrow.

1585
01:07:50,510 --> 01:07:53,449
This season is a spin-off.

1586
01:07:53,450 --> 01:07:55,380
The title of the spin-off is...

1587
01:07:55,510 --> 01:07:58,049
Fresh Off the Sea in Calape.

1588
01:07:58,050 --> 01:08:00,219
- Calape.
- So tomorrow,

1589
01:08:00,220 --> 01:08:01,849
just like the title,

1590
01:08:01,850 --> 01:08:03,319
we'll go to Calape.

1591
01:08:03,320 --> 01:08:04,919
What is Calape?

1592
01:08:04,920 --> 01:08:06,830
- It's the name of a region.
- I see.

1593
01:08:08,190 --> 01:08:10,960
(A peaceful region in Bohol)

1594
01:08:11,560 --> 01:08:15,499
(Calape encompasses the ocean and the forest.)

1595
01:08:15,500 --> 01:08:16,869
What is Calape?

1596
01:08:16,870 --> 01:08:18,299
(We need to go to Calape and do something else?)

1597
01:08:18,300 --> 01:08:19,369
Calape?

1598
01:08:19,370 --> 01:08:20,740
(Looking it up)

1599
01:08:20,910 --> 01:08:22,839
A field, trees, or an orchard.

1600
01:08:22,840 --> 01:08:24,720
- It must be something like that.
- I think so.

1601
01:08:25,380 --> 01:08:26,850
Coconut maybe?

1602
01:08:27,710 --> 01:08:29,510
Are we going to have to harvest coconuts?

1603
01:08:30,480 --> 01:08:31,619
Or bananas?

1604
01:08:31,620 --> 01:08:32,950
(Or bananas?)

1605
01:08:35,020 --> 01:08:36,120
It must be mangoes.

1606
01:08:37,390 --> 01:08:38,460
Mangoes.

1607
01:08:38,620 --> 01:08:41,090
Jun Myun might eat it while working.

1608
01:08:44,100 --> 01:08:46,699
(Mango Park, join us.)

1609
01:08:46,700 --> 01:08:48,770
(Let's eat together.)

1610
01:08:49,230 --> 01:08:51,939
Coconut, pineapple, mango...

1611
01:08:51,940 --> 01:08:53,199
(It must be one of the tropical fruits.)

1612
01:08:53,200 --> 01:08:54,209
Durian.

1613
01:08:54,210 --> 01:08:55,210
I say it's mango.

1614
01:08:55,211 --> 01:08:56,740
(Salivating)

1615
01:08:59,340 --> 01:09:00,349
- It's a farm.
- Well,

1616
01:09:00,350 --> 01:09:02,279
whatever it is, you must include mangoes somehow.

1617
01:09:02,280 --> 01:09:03,749
Yes. It's a farm.

1618
01:09:03,750 --> 01:09:05,580
(What kind of labor will they do in Calape?)

1619
01:09:06,420 --> 01:09:08,349
(The four siblings come back from their dinner.)

1620
01:09:08,350 --> 01:09:10,460
- I'll wash quickly.
- Okay.

1621
01:09:11,760 --> 01:09:14,160
(As soon as he returns, he changes out of the party outfit.)

1622
01:09:14,730 --> 01:09:18,560
(Everyone is getting ready to rest.)

1623
01:09:23,770 --> 01:09:26,000
(She isn't sleeping.)

1624
01:09:26,540 --> 01:09:28,870
(She's listening to music.)

1625
01:09:33,710 --> 01:09:35,750
(The ukulele, which was hung on the wall, fell.)

1626
01:09:36,650 --> 01:09:39,680
(She doesn't care and goes back to listening to the music.)

1627
01:09:42,490 --> 01:09:44,420
- I can't be bothered to wash.
- Me too.

1628
01:09:44,490 --> 01:09:45,660
I don't want to wash.

1629
01:09:46,290 --> 01:09:48,990
How dare you act cute? Go and shower.

1630
01:09:49,760 --> 01:09:51,499
Why is it so bothersome to shower, Jung Ah?

1631
01:09:51,500 --> 01:09:52,500
Me too.

1632
01:09:52,501 --> 01:09:54,099
(Squirming to express her distaste in shower)

1633
01:09:54,100 --> 01:09:55,370
Shower after having fun, then.

1634
01:09:56,370 --> 01:09:57,699
- Are you done washing?
- Yes.

1635
01:09:57,700 --> 01:09:59,169
(Dex who finished washing and came to have fun)

1636
01:09:59,170 --> 01:10:01,170
I don't want to shower.

1637
01:10:01,240 --> 01:10:02,310
You haven't showered yet?

1638
01:10:03,380 --> 01:10:06,040
- Good job today.
- Good job.

1639
01:10:10,680 --> 01:10:12,850
Tomorrow is already the third day.

1640
01:10:12,920 --> 01:10:16,190
We're leaving after two nights.

1641
01:10:17,120 --> 01:10:19,059
It feels short.

1642
01:10:19,060 --> 01:10:20,606
(Their time in Bohol feels shorter for some reason.)

1643
01:10:20,630 --> 01:10:21,789
Goodness.

1644
01:10:21,790 --> 01:10:23,590
(Hye Yoon suddenly has a flower in her hair.)

1645
01:10:23,630 --> 01:10:25,360
(Staring)

1646
01:10:25,730 --> 01:10:28,930
Since she was 17, Hye Yoon...

1647
01:10:29,200 --> 01:10:30,600
- Started acting?
- Yes.

1648
01:10:31,200 --> 01:10:32,520
She's been acting for many years.

1649
01:10:32,740 --> 01:10:33,809
You've done it for a long time.

1650
01:10:33,810 --> 01:10:34,839
(Hye Yoon has been acting for 14 years already.)

1651
01:10:34,840 --> 01:10:36,760
You played student roles for a long time, right?

1652
01:10:37,080 --> 01:10:39,439
Yes, even after I became an adult.

1653
01:10:39,440 --> 01:10:41,680
Student 1, Student 2. She's played countless of those.

1654
01:10:42,010 --> 01:10:43,519
She really did a lot.

1655
01:10:43,520 --> 01:10:45,150
(Hye Yoon started with small roles.)

1656
01:10:45,480 --> 01:10:48,620
I really liked it when you went on "You Quiz on the Block."

1657
01:10:49,020 --> 01:10:52,290
I didn't know you were an unknown actress for so long.

1658
01:10:52,790 --> 01:10:54,459
Exactly. People think...

1659
01:10:54,460 --> 01:10:57,200
you suddenly appeared with "SKY Castle."

1660
01:10:57,900 --> 01:11:00,330
(Hye Yoon went through many years as an unknown actress.)

1661
01:11:00,470 --> 01:11:01,999
The process was so hard.

1662
01:11:02,000 --> 01:11:03,639
I got rejected because of my height...

1663
01:11:03,640 --> 01:11:05,440
for shootings and auditions.

1664
01:11:05,570 --> 01:11:08,469
Because of my height. "Her height is a bit..."

1665
01:11:08,470 --> 01:11:10,309
That happened so many times.

1666
01:11:10,310 --> 01:11:12,240
But even then,

1667
01:11:12,780 --> 01:11:15,110
when they mentioned my height, I just thought...

1668
01:11:15,180 --> 01:11:16,279
the role wasn't for me.

1669
01:11:16,280 --> 01:11:19,750
I'm sure there's someone out there who loves my height too.

1670
01:11:19,850 --> 01:11:21,450
That's what I thought.

1671
01:11:21,850 --> 01:11:22,950
I'm 159cm.

1672
01:11:23,760 --> 01:11:24,790
Compare your heights.

1673
01:11:26,290 --> 01:11:28,189
- You...
- I'm shorter than 160cm.

1674
01:11:28,190 --> 01:11:29,660
- Me too.
- You do look it.

1675
01:11:30,160 --> 01:11:31,260
"You do look it."

1676
01:11:31,960 --> 01:11:33,906
(Suddenly comparing heights in the middle of the night)

1677
01:11:33,930 --> 01:11:36,270
Your shoulders are at a similar level.

1678
01:11:37,700 --> 01:11:38,769
Goodness.

1679
01:11:38,770 --> 01:11:40,046
You're really about one centimeter taller.

1680
01:11:40,070 --> 01:11:42,139
- Really? Jun Myun is?
- Yes, around one centimeter.

1681
01:11:42,140 --> 01:11:44,009
- Jun Myun is taller.
- Is she 158cm?

1682
01:11:44,010 --> 01:11:46,380
Isn't Hye Yoon's short height her charm?

1683
01:11:46,680 --> 01:11:49,410
Yes. Tiptoeing to kiss the actor and so on.

1684
01:11:49,710 --> 01:11:51,319
That's so cute. You know what I mean, right?

1685
01:11:51,320 --> 01:11:52,620
- And...
- Tiptoeing like this.

1686
01:11:52,680 --> 01:11:54,090
It's 11pm now.

1687
01:11:54,250 --> 01:11:56,219
I should shower. I'm going to bed first.

1688
01:11:56,220 --> 01:11:57,820
- Okay.
- Good night.

1689
01:11:58,420 --> 01:12:00,780
(Jun Myun leaves, and the three remain in the living room.)

1690
01:12:02,090 --> 01:12:05,030
(A new guest arrives to fill Jun Myun's empty spot.)

1691
01:12:05,260 --> 01:12:07,400
(Watching them)

1692
01:12:07,800 --> 01:12:08,970
It's a cat.

1693
01:12:10,870 --> 01:12:11,999
How cute.

1694
01:12:12,000 --> 01:12:13,670
(She's drawn to it like magic.)

1695
01:12:14,070 --> 01:12:16,440
(Positioning herself right in front of the window)

1696
01:12:17,740 --> 01:12:21,150
(They just look at each other forlornly.)

1697
01:12:21,910 --> 01:12:23,850
Hye Yoon likes cats. She's a cat mom.

1698
01:12:25,920 --> 01:12:27,120
(I'm leaving, Korean cat mom.)

1699
01:12:29,890 --> 01:12:32,320
(I'm here this time.)

1700
01:12:35,890 --> 01:12:38,029
Gosh, they're having a neighborhood party.

1701
01:12:38,030 --> 01:12:39,099
You're right.

1702
01:12:39,100 --> 01:12:40,329
How many are there?

1703
01:12:40,330 --> 01:12:42,830
(Having a Bohol dog gathering)

1704
01:12:42,900 --> 01:12:43,970
Four.

1705
01:12:46,300 --> 01:12:48,870
(They get caught right away, so they quickly disperse.)

1706
01:12:49,540 --> 01:12:52,216
(After the animal guests leave, it's just the three of them again.)

1707
01:12:52,240 --> 01:12:53,479
How old were you when you got married?

1708
01:12:53,480 --> 01:12:54,510
Thirty-five.

1709
01:12:55,150 --> 01:12:57,950
I met him when I was 34.

1710
01:12:59,320 --> 01:13:01,400
How many years and above is long for dating someone?

1711
01:13:02,390 --> 01:13:03,450
Seven to eight years.

1712
01:13:03,560 --> 01:13:04,859
- Seven to eight years.
- Ten. Seven to eight years,

1713
01:13:04,860 --> 01:13:06,120
up to ten years.

1714
01:13:06,790 --> 01:13:09,159
Jin Young, you should do six months.

1715
01:13:09,160 --> 01:13:10,400
(Of dating and getting married)

1716
01:13:10,600 --> 01:13:12,106
She was just talking about people dating for 7 to 8 years.

1717
01:13:12,130 --> 01:13:15,370
- But that's way too short.
- Jin Young should do six months.

1718
01:13:16,070 --> 01:13:17,800
Have you ever cried because of a woman?

1719
01:13:19,000 --> 01:13:20,069
I don't think I have.

1720
01:13:20,070 --> 01:13:21,740
Really?

1721
01:13:22,070 --> 01:13:25,009
So you don't know this feeling?

1722
01:13:25,010 --> 01:13:26,339
- It hurts here.
- Your heart...

1723
01:13:26,340 --> 01:13:27,679
- Like your throat hurts.
- Why?

1724
01:13:27,680 --> 01:13:28,979
Because you scream?

1725
01:13:28,980 --> 01:13:31,019
- No.
- It's when you like someone...

1726
01:13:31,020 --> 01:13:33,179
so much that your heart hurts.

1727
01:13:33,180 --> 01:13:35,460
You don't know what an aching heart feels like? The pain?

1728
01:13:35,850 --> 01:13:37,290
- That's not a bad thing.
- No.

1729
01:13:38,690 --> 01:13:40,490
But you're sad.

1730
01:13:40,590 --> 01:13:43,630
But you don't always marry the person you feel that way about.

1731
01:13:45,400 --> 01:13:48,929
To me, marriage feels like...

1732
01:13:48,930 --> 01:13:49,969
the College Scholastic Ability Test.

1733
01:13:49,970 --> 01:13:52,570
I thought I'd never take the College Scholastic Ability Test.

1734
01:13:53,100 --> 01:13:55,440
It's such an important and huge occasion.

1735
01:13:55,540 --> 01:13:57,110
So I couldn't believe that...

1736
01:13:57,310 --> 01:13:58,810
it would come to me.

1737
01:14:00,350 --> 01:14:02,609
- And then...
- So marriage doesn't feel real.

1738
01:14:02,610 --> 01:14:04,850
No, I can't even imagine it.

1739
01:14:05,220 --> 01:14:07,919
Like "Would I ever experience that?"

1740
01:14:07,920 --> 01:14:09,166
(Marriage feels so far away that Hye Yoon can't even imagine it.)

1741
01:14:09,190 --> 01:14:12,059
I never thought I'd become a father.

1742
01:14:12,060 --> 01:14:13,196
(I never thought I'd get married, let alone become a father.)

1743
01:14:13,220 --> 01:14:14,859
But if it comes to me, I think I could do it.

1744
01:14:14,860 --> 01:14:17,999
- Marriage...
- Marriage isn't the answer.

1745
01:14:18,000 --> 01:14:19,760
(Marriage isn't the answer to life.)

1746
01:14:20,100 --> 01:14:23,030
But when you love someone,

1747
01:14:23,330 --> 01:14:26,640
that person makes the world seem beautiful.

1748
01:14:27,740 --> 01:14:30,539
And the way you perceive the world changes...

1749
01:14:30,540 --> 01:14:31,610
when you have children.

1750
01:14:33,480 --> 01:14:36,410
I'm sure it's the same for men too, but that's motherhood.

1751
01:14:37,120 --> 01:14:38,279
Marriage is something worth experiencing.

1752
01:14:38,280 --> 01:14:40,350
(Jung Ah gives them wholehearted advice.)

1753
01:14:40,590 --> 01:14:44,090
Getting married changes your life.

1754
01:14:45,460 --> 01:14:46,759
Why don't we wrap up for the night?

1755
01:14:46,760 --> 01:14:48,190
All right, let's go to sleep.

1756
01:14:48,630 --> 01:14:51,730
(They go to sleep so they're ready for tomorrow.)

1757
01:14:53,930 --> 01:14:57,600
(The sky slowly turns blue.)

1758
01:14:58,470 --> 01:15:01,470
(It's their third morning in Bohol.)

1759
01:15:03,270 --> 01:15:05,880
(As always, this morning in Bohol is full of energy.)

1760
01:15:07,210 --> 01:15:10,110
(People are busy starting their day.)

1761
01:15:11,950 --> 01:15:14,890
(What kind of day do the siblings have ahead of them?)

1762
01:15:16,320 --> 01:15:19,120
(Wake up!)

1763
01:15:24,660 --> 01:15:28,900
(Rooster crowing)

1764
01:15:29,930 --> 01:15:32,870
(Jung Ah woke up at the rooster's morning alarm.)

1765
01:15:34,170 --> 01:15:36,510
(She's the first one to get ready.)

1766
01:15:37,080 --> 01:15:38,439
(Stretching)

1767
01:15:38,440 --> 01:15:40,280
(After a quick stretch, )

1768
01:15:41,250 --> 01:15:44,380
(Jung Ah mops the floor.)

1769
01:15:45,350 --> 01:15:48,620
(Don't forget the kitchen.)

1770
01:15:50,020 --> 01:15:53,220
(Jung Ah's morning routine remains the same, even in Bohol.)

1771
01:15:55,090 --> 01:15:58,030
(Jun Myun wakes up.)

1772
01:15:58,600 --> 01:16:00,430
(The younger siblings are also up...)

1773
01:16:00,630 --> 01:16:03,570
(and quickly getting ready to leave.)

1774
01:16:04,500 --> 01:16:06,539
(The 1st thing on their schedule for Day 3 is...)

1775
01:16:06,540 --> 01:16:08,540
(labor.)

1776
01:16:08,640 --> 01:16:11,239
Today's outfit of the day.

1777
01:16:11,240 --> 01:16:12,309
(Hye Yoon's OOTD)

1778
01:16:12,310 --> 01:16:15,810
(Pink, cute, labor outfit of the day)

1779
01:16:16,050 --> 01:16:17,680
Hello.

1780
01:16:17,780 --> 01:16:19,720
Did you sleep well?

1781
01:16:21,090 --> 01:16:24,290
(Before they leave, she's unpacking a pair of shoes to wear today.)

1782
01:16:25,260 --> 01:16:27,130
(Looking around)

1783
01:16:28,530 --> 01:16:31,130
(Hye Yoon is looking for something.)

1784
01:16:31,260 --> 01:16:35,929
Did you perhaps... My shoes.

1785
01:16:35,930 --> 01:16:37,269
There's only one of them.

1786
01:16:37,270 --> 01:16:39,339
- You only have that one?
- What's going on?

1787
01:16:39,340 --> 01:16:41,580
(Kim Hye Yoon, the youngest, She's suddenly Cinderella.)

1788
01:16:42,840 --> 01:16:43,879
My shoe.

1789
01:16:43,880 --> 01:16:45,160
(Hye Yoon's shoe is actually...)

1790
01:16:46,910 --> 01:16:48,850
(Around 3am in the morning)

1791
01:16:49,650 --> 01:16:52,520
(The puppy came over to play again.)

1792
01:16:53,620 --> 01:16:57,260
(It walks up to the front door.)

1793
01:16:58,190 --> 01:17:01,030
(Rustling)

1794
01:17:01,130 --> 01:17:03,460
(The rustling sound seems suspicious.)

1795
01:17:04,360 --> 01:17:06,830
(The puppy had something in its mouth.)

1796
01:17:07,170 --> 01:17:08,970
(It's Hye Yoon's shoe.)

1797
01:17:09,800 --> 01:17:11,600
(It picks up the shoe in its mouth...)

1798
01:17:11,770 --> 01:17:14,340
(and runs off with it.)

1799
01:17:15,210 --> 01:17:18,210
I think we should bring our shoes inside.

1800
01:17:18,310 --> 01:17:19,909
A puppy took one of my shoes last night.

1801
01:17:19,910 --> 01:17:21,479
Goodness.

1802
01:17:21,480 --> 01:17:23,326
I went outside and there was only one of these.

1803
01:17:23,350 --> 01:17:25,249
So I was like, "I only have one of my shoes."

1804
01:17:25,250 --> 01:17:26,780
Mine is the only one this happened to.

1805
01:17:27,890 --> 01:17:29,850
(She lost her mind.)

1806
01:17:30,020 --> 01:17:31,719
This is so funny.

1807
01:17:31,720 --> 01:17:33,236
(There's never a dull moment at the siblings' house.)

1808
01:17:33,260 --> 01:17:35,459
- Good morning.
- You're up.

1809
01:17:35,460 --> 01:17:37,160
Yes.

1810
01:17:37,400 --> 01:17:38,600
- Hello.
- Hey.

1811
01:17:39,530 --> 01:17:40,530
Did you sleep well?

1812
01:17:41,730 --> 01:17:43,630
(He checks the mirror...)

1813
01:17:46,840 --> 01:17:49,440
(and puts something on his face.)

1814
01:17:49,640 --> 01:17:51,180
What are you putting on by yourself?

1815
01:17:51,480 --> 01:17:53,179
Sunscreen. Did you put it on?

1816
01:17:53,180 --> 01:17:54,249
Not yet. We have to.

1817
01:17:54,250 --> 01:17:55,949
- I have to too. I didn't, yet.
- Before we leave...

1818
01:17:55,950 --> 01:17:57,379
for work, we have to put sunscreen on.

1819
01:17:57,380 --> 01:17:59,780
- This is a sweat-proof sun stick.
